This epic tracks a set of composable renderables/layout helpers inspired by `rich_rust`.

Unlike a widget zoo, these are meant to be small building blocks that make it easier to implement the **agent harness essential widgets** in Phase 5.

## Reference Source
- `legacy_reference_library_code/rich_rust/`

## Plan Alignment
Plan Phase 5 requires:
- `Renderable` trait
- Panel
- Text wrapping
- Table (basic)
- Viewport/TextInput (harness essentials)

This epic’s renderables are optional but useful for building those features with less bespoke code.

## Scope
Renderables in this epic are expected to:
- render into `Frame`/`Buffer` deterministically
- have clear layout contracts
- be testable via snapshot tests (frame grids)

## Non-Goals
- porting every rich renderable
- shipping “pretty” renderables that aren’t needed for the harness before Gate 1–2

## Success Criteria
- [ ] Each renderable has deterministic snapshot tests and is integrated into the widget layer.
- [ ] Dependencies are explicit (renderables depend on core primitives, not vice versa).
